## Change 5 — Minimal animations

Add subtle, tasteful animations that match the paper aesthetic.
NO: bouncing, scaling, color flashing, parallax, or anything that feels like a SaaS landing page.
YES: gentle fade-ins, soft underline reveals, a single cursor blink.

### 5a — Page content fade-in

In `app/globals.css`, add:

```css
@keyframes fadein {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(6px); }
  to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}

main {
  animation: fadein 0.5s ease forwards;
}
```

This fades the entire main content area in on navigation. 0.5s, translateY of only 6px —
imperceptible on first glance but makes page transitions feel intentional.

### 5b — Nav link underline reveal on hover

Replace the existing hover underline on nav links with a CSS-only slide-in underline.
In `app/globals.css` (or inline in Sidebar.tsx via style tag):

```css
.nav-link {
  position: relative;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.nav-link::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  bottom: -2px;
  left: 0;
  width: 0;
  height: 1px;
  background: var(--fg);
  transition: width 0.2s ease;
}

.nav-link:hover::after,
.nav-link.active::after {
  width: 100%;
}
```

Apply class `nav-link` to all sidebar navigation `<a>` tags.
For the active link, also apply `active` class (already determined by `usePathname`).

### 5c — Project list entry fade-in stagger

In `components/ProjectList.tsx`, add a CSS animation delay per item using inline style:

```tsx
<li
  key={i}
  style={{
    animationDelay: `${i * 60}ms`,
    animation: "fadein 0.4s ease both",
  }}
>
```

This staggers each project entry by 60ms — subtle enough to feel like loading,
not like a showreel. Requires the `fadein` keyframe from 5a to be defined globally.

### 5d — Details/summary toggle transition

In `app/globals.css`, add a smooth open animation for the early projects dropdown:

```css
details.early-projects[open] ol {
  animation: fadein 0.3s ease forwards;
}
```

